<h2> Introduction </h2>

I am a Ph.D. candidate at <a
href="http://wwwhost.cc.utexas.edu/"> UT-Austin </a> in the
<a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/"> Department of Computer
Sciences.</a>
My supervising professor is <a
href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/misra"> Jayadev Misra </a> and my
dissertation topic is 
<a href="ftp://ftp.cs.utexas.edu/pub/techreports/tr94-10.ps.Z"> 
<em> Real-Time UNITY</em>. </a>
I am a member of Professor Misra's 
<a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/psp"> PSP research group. </a>
<p>
I am extending the 
<a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/psp/welcome.html#unitysec"> UNITY </a>
theory in order to express finite time bounds
on the usual UNITY operators for progress and safety.  I am also
interested in functional programming languages, partial order
semantics and automated theorem proving.

